<img data-lazy-fallback="1" decoding="async" width="700" height="400" class="wp-image-1955866" style="width: 600px;" src="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Peter-Obi-1.webp" alt="Peter Obi" srcset="https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Peter-Obi-1.webp?width=700&amp;auto_optimize=medium 700w, https://cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2022/10/Peter-Obi-1-300x171.webp?width=300&amp;auto_optimize=medium 300w" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px"  /> By Nwafor Sunday As the country approaches its slated general election, the candidate of the Labour Party, LP, Mr Peter Obi has cautioned Nigerians not to hand over a ‘sick country to a sick person’. He advised that Nigerians should vote wisely, noting that it would be destructive if a sick person is elected to rule in the next four years. Obi, made the appeal in an interactive session with students of the University of Nigeria, Nsukka, UNN, Business School, in Enugu on Thursday. The former governor advised that Nigerians should desist from voting in someone who cannot stand for 30 minutes. His words:  “This country is sick and should not be handed over to a sick person. I am not saying that everyone is sick. We have been here for over two hours, we don’t want people who can’t stand for 30 minutes. “If you said you will fight corruption, let’s go to the road you have passed and see what is remaining there after you left. “This year’s election must be based on competence. This job requires physical and mental energy, it is not a retirement job.”  Obi shades Tinubu over educational records, health status In "News" FORMER Governor of Anambra State, Mr. Peter Obi has called for attitudinal change towards education among Nigerians. He decried the subsisting situation of, “the lack of treating education with the seriousness it deserves by classifying money spent on it as expenditure rather than investment”. In "News" “Atiku is 100% fit and in super form healthwise. The British Government invited the leading presidential candidate, Atiku Abubakar, just like they had invited Bola Tinubu and Peter Obi earlier." In "News"